How To Tuesday How to Make Seaweed Chips Fun FactThe chemical composition ofseaweed is so close to human blood plasma that they are excellent at regulating and purifying our blood INGREDIENTS 12 nori sheets1 4 cup water1 Tsesame oil3 cloves garlicmincedPinch ground cayenne pepperSalt to tasteDIRECTIONS 1 Preheat the oven to 275 FCover two large baking sheets with parchment paper or aluminum foil 2 Place six sheets of norishiny side upon the baking sheetWith a pastry brushlightly brush the shiny side of the nori with waterbe sure to reach the edgesthen carefully align another sheet of nori on top and press them togetherRepeat with the remaining sheets until they are buddied up 3 Using kitchen shears or a sharp knifecut the nori into one inch stripsthen cut those strips in half crosswiseYou will end up with about 42 chipsArrange the chips in a single layer on the baking sheets 4 In a small bowlcombine the garlicsesame oiland cayenneUse the pastry brush to coat the top of the chipsthen sprinkle generously with saltUse your fingers to sprinkle sesame seeds across the tops of the chips 5 Place on the middle rack of the ovenand bake for 15 20 minutesThey will turn a deepglossy greenRemove from the oventasteand sprinkle with salt if you likeAllow them to cool before eating for maximum crunchEat up enjoyLCNHowToTuesdayHowToTuesdayseaweedseaweedchips

Throughout history people have flocked to coastal areas for foodForaging for food can be rewarding here Even if I don t catch any fish I often forage for seaweed when I m on the coast I normally use it as an ingredient with pasta either blanched or friedLast time I wanted to do something else with it so I made chips out of it It s very easy to make and it tastes greatSeaweed contains a high amount of iodine which can be healthy for youMany people suffer from iodine deficiency so in that sense it can be very beneficialJust make sure you don t eat too much of it too oftenThe high amount of iodine can cause iodine poisoningAnd beware not to eat it at all if you have Metabolic disorderThat said it also contains both vitamins ABCE and K as well a big variety of mineralsamino acids and omega 3s If you want to try making seaweed chips here s an easy recipe for you The only ingredients you need areSeaweedVirgin olive oil and Sea saltStart by cutting the top shoots into bite sized piecesPour a few spoons of virgin olive oil in a bowltoss the seaweed around in it and add some sea salt to itTake out the seaweed and let the oil drip off before you spread it out on a baking trayPut it in a preheated oven at 100 degrees C for about an hour and voil  scandinavia

Tunasandwich Yes indeedy And it tastes like the real thing This recipe serves 4 Ingredientsciabatta bread 2 3 of a can of green or young jackfruit1 2 can of chickpeas3 sticks of celery1 4 of a white onion3 tablespoons of hummusfresh cracked black peppera pinch of salta splash of apple cider vinegarand 1 2 a package of roasted seaweed snacks chipsRecipe Thoroughly rinse the jackfruit at least three timesCut off the tough part on one endShred the Jackfruit and remove the seeds with your handsThoroughly rinse the chickpeas at least three timesthen smash them on a cutting boardthey should still be recognizableCombine the two ingredients togetherForm the mixture into medium to large sized ballsthen squeeze out as much liquid as possiblePut it in the refrigerator until you re ready to use it Dice your celery and onions into very small piecesShred up your seaweed snacksAdd these ingredients to a bowl with the Jackfruit and smashed chickpeasAdd your hummusblack peppersaltand apple cider vinegarStir the ingredients until everything is evenly distributedTaste the mixture to make sure it is well seasonedYou can use vegan mayonnaise instead of hummusYou can substitute the apple cider vinegar for lemon juice Toast your bread on both sides with your choice of oil in a non stick pan or cast iron skilletSpread your tuna salad on to the breadthen eatThis recipe took about 20 to 30 minutes for me to prepareIdeally it should have been done when I wasn t starving LOLIt definitely hit the spotThe bonus for me was the fact that I still got in my carbsproteinand fiberI hope you try it out jackfruit chickpeasciabatta ciabattabread celeryonionsblackpepper salt hummus applecidervinegarseaweedsnacksseaweedchips vegantuna vegan

DulsePalmaria palmatais one of my favourite seaweeds and I ll be teaching it this weekendIt gives a great saltyumami flavour to breaddips and so much more Have you ever harvested fresh dulseIt s also beautiful to look at in the waterThis Sunday participants will get to try dulse freshdried and in breadYou ll get to see it in situ and learn where it likes to growhow to sustainably harvest it and how to dry and store itDulse is packed with nutritionis high in proteinvitamin A and ironIt also contains potassiumB vitaminscalcium and manganeseI share more about itincluding recipes in myseaweedbookand plenty more in the flesh on Sunday s courseDetails and how to book on my website Meanwhile here s a dulse recipe for you Baba Ghanoush with Dulse Seaweed An Arabian dish perfect for dipping freshly cut vegetables intoor spreading onto breadInspired by Daverick Leggett s recipe and given a seaweed twistIngredients3 aubergines3 cloves of garlic2 tbsp dark tahiniJuice of 2 lemonsSea salt and pepper to taste5 g dried and ground dulse seaweedOlive oil to garnish and to tasteBurn the auberginesEither on the highest temperature in the oven or on an open flame until they go soft and squidgyScoop out the insidesor peel off the skin and blend the flesh with the rest of the ingredientsDrizzle with a good olive oil and serveLasts well for a weekif you hide it and don t eat it all at once

tuna maki rolls at popular sushi restaurantswith the passion fruit rendering that extra burst of savor I also tried a portion of thepokenachos which served crisp and crunchy tempura batteredseaweedchipstopped with both minced tuna and salmon sashimi marinated in spicy soytobikopankospring onion and a dressing ofwasabimayoAgain great play on texture and full of flavour
